 is the depths of failure, but it's not too bad,

12
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:33,600
 not too hard to fix it, so we just gotta fix it.

13
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:38,360
 So the problem is if the browser sends a post request

14
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:40,500
 and it gets back a 200 and a page of HTML,

15
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,420
 which is exactly what we just did,

16
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:44,820
 and then you hit the refresh button on your browser,

17
00:00:44,820 --> 00:00:46,880
 the browser is going to resend the post request.

18
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:50,200
 If you go back, I said post requests are things that change.

19
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:53,400
 So for example, if you are transferring money

20
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,800
 from your account to someone else's

21
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:57,580
 and then you hit the transfer button, it's a post,

22
00:00:57,580 --> 00:01:01,080
 and the money gets transferred, and then transfer successful.

23
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:04,600
 And then if you hit refresh, you're gonna post it again.

24
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,760
 And so the refresh basically reruns

25
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:08,440
 the entire previous transaction.

26
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:11,440
 It doesn't just grab the page, it sends the post data again.

27
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:14,860
 So if you transferred $100 in one post and you hit refresh,

28
00:01:14,860 --> 00:01:16,820
 you're gonna transfer $100 again.

29
00:01:16,820 --> 00:01:19,280
 So what happens is is that because the browsers know

30
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:22,440
 that posts are potentially dangerous to the server,

31
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:25,160
 the user will get a pop-up, not from you,

32
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:28,160
 but from the browser to say, hey,

33
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:30,960
 this person who built this server application

34
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:33,080
 left you sitting on a post, and you hit refresh,

35
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,740
 and I'm gonna about post it again.

36
00:01:34,740 --> 00:01:36,880
 So are you sure you really wanna do that?

37
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:39,500
 And the problem is the user doesn't even know what a post is,

38
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:43,020
 barely knows what's a refresh, and it looks like a mess.

39
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:45,960
 So the way to do this is you go to the page,

40
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:49,760
 you type in 42, you hit submit query,

