 and it'll say congratulations, and you look at it,

42
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:55,100
 and then you press the refresh button,

43
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:58,280
 the refresh button, the reload button,

44
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:01,060
 and you press the reload button, and it says,

45
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:03,880
 to display this page, Firefox must send information

46
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:05,720
 that will repeat an action, such as a search order

47
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:07,720
 confirmation that was performed earlier,

48
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,960
 or a money transfer.

49
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,280
 That is not a message from your application.

50
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,400
 That is literally because your application

51
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,960
 was a little sloppy, and Firefox is like,

52
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,760
 I'm really not sure if we should do this,

53
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:21,400
 so I'm gonna ask the user, but it doesn't exactly know

54
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:24,760
 what to ask the user, it doesn't know what you just did,

55
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:29,160
 and so it's a yucky message, and what we wanna do

56
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,760
 as programmers is avoid this.

57
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:33,080
 We want all the message, all the user experience

58
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:36,120
 coming from us, not having the browsers take over

59
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:39,240
 some of these things, and so it's just bad practice

60
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:44,240
 in general to send a 200 post, to take a post request,

61
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:48,400
 and then send a 200 with an HTML page back, okay?

62
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:52,080
 And so it's just ugly, and it sits in the browser ass,

63
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:55,000
 it's out of your control, it's ugly, it's bad usability,

64
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,800
 so we can do a little bit of work to make this never happen.

65
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,440
 So that's what we wanna do here.

66
